					<description><![CDATA[In reply to &lt;a href=&quot;https://jamesclear.vercel.app/threshold-theory#comment-11865&quot;&gt;Binh&lt;/a&gt;.

So many people wait until somebody passes the ball. (Not just in basketball.) What if that day never comes? Studying is preparation. But preparation alone won&#039;t you get the ball.

Don&#039;t wait until you get the ball.
Don&#039;t wait until you get a raise.
Don&#039;t wait until you get asked for a date.

You have to go for it yourself.

(And maybe you fail and try again. And again - again and again. Until you finally succeed. This is called practice... and nothing in the world can take its place.)]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>In reply to <a href="https://jamesclear.vercel.app/threshold-theory#comment-11865">Binh</a>.</p>
<p>So many people wait until somebody passes the ball. (Not just in basketball.) What if that day never comes? Studying is preparation. But preparation alone won&#8217;t you get the ball.</p>
<p>Don&#8217;t wait until you get the ball.<br />
Don&#8217;t wait until you get a raise.<br />
Don&#8217;t wait until you get asked for a date.</p>
<p>You have to go for it yourself.</p>
<p>(And maybe you fail and try again. And again &#8211; again and again. Until you finally succeed. This is called practice&#8230; and nothing in the world can take its place.)</p>
